title: Rancho Mirage Housing Element and Supporting Documents

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. All Documents submitted to Cal. HCD by any employee of the City of Rancho Mirage between April 2019 and the present, concerning Rancho Mirage's Housing Element
2. All Documents submitted to Cal. HCD by any employee of the City of Rancho Mirage between 2019 and the present, reflecting Rancho Mirage's Annual Housing Element Progress Report
3. All Documents submitted to Cal. HCD by any employee of the City of Rancho Mirage between 2019 and the present, making any representations that the City of Rancho Mirage is taking steps to create affordable housing in Rancho Mirage.
4. All Documents submitted to Cal. HCD by any employee of the City of Rancho Mirage between 2019 and the present, making any representations that the City of Rancho Mirage is taking steps to affirmatively further fair housing in Rancho Mirage.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Annette Morasch

title: 2010 Kelly Elementary School Gunfire Incident Report

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: 2010 Kelly Elementary School Gunfire Incident Report
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The incident report and any investigative reports, including supplements such as police narratives, produced in relation to the shooting incident at Kelly Elementary School on 10/8/2010.

In the event that there are fees, I would request a waiver, as I am a member of a nonprofit media outlet and these records will be used in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. 

I would prefer the request filed electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,
Daniella Jimenez
Investigative Reporting Workshop.
